- Generates 50 unique bot identities with randomized usernames and personas.

#### [NEW] [bots/page.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/app/# Phase 30: System Audit & Hardening

This phase addresses the critical technical gaps identified during our platform audit, specifically focusing on SEO discoverability, UI performance, and user experience during content creation.

## User Review Required

> [!WARNING]
> Implementing Adaptive Bitrate Streaming (HLS / `.m3u8`) requires a significant re-architecture of the `ffmpeg` video processor ([lib/video-processor.ts](file:///C:/GOLive/lib/video-processor.ts)) and the Cloudflare R2 upload pipeline ([app/api/upload/multipart/route.ts](file:///C:/GOLive/app/api/upload/multipart/route.ts)). Instead of uploading a single `.mp4`, we would need to generate and upload an index file and dozens of [.ts](file:///C:/GOLive/lib/tags.ts) segments.
> **Decision Needed:** Should we proceed with the complex HLS video re-architecture now, or prioritize the high-impact front-end fixes (SEO Metadata, Lazy Loading, Background Uploads) to ensure immediate virality and performance?

## Proposed Changes

---

### SEO & Metadata Infrastructure

To ensure VibeStream links (Watch and Profile pages) unfurl correctly with dynamic thumbnails and titles on platforms like Twitter, Discord, and iMessage:

#### [MODIFY] [app/watch/[id]/page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Walt%20&%20Carter/.gemini/antigravity/playground/sonic-zenith/app/watch/%5Bid%5D/page.tsx)
- **Addition**: Export a Next.js [generateMetadata({ params })](file:///C:/GOLive/app/profile/%5Busername%5D/page.tsx#17-64) function.
- **Logic**: Fetch the specific video by ID server-side before rendering. Map the `video.title`, `video.description`, and `video.thumbnail_url` to Open Graph (`og:title`, `og:image`, `og:description`) and Twitter Card meta tags.

#### [MODIFY] [app/profile/[username]/page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Walt%20&%20Carter/.gemini/antigravity/playground/sonic-zenith/app/profile/%5Busername%5D/page.tsx)
- **Addition**: Export [generateMetadata({ params })](file:///C:/GOLive/app/profile/%5Busername%5D/page.tsx#17-64).
- **Logic**: Fetch the specific user profile. Map their `display_name`, `bio`, and `avatar_url` to accurate social sharing cards.

---

### UI Performance (Lazy Loading)

To aggressively reduce First Contentful Paint (FCP) and prevent massive initial payloads when rendering the [HomeClient](file:///C:/GOLive/app/HomeClient.tsx#13-242) feed or `Trending` grids:

#### [MODIFY] [components/VideoCard.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/components/VideoCard.tsx)
- **Implementation**: Integrate `react-intersection-observer` (or the native Intersection Observer API).
### SEO Metadata
#### [MODIFY] [app/watch/[id]/page.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/app/watch/[id]/page.tsx)
- Export Next.js [generateMetadata](file:///C:/GOLive/app/profile/%5Busername%5D/page.tsx#17-64) function.
- Fetch video details by ID and populate Open Graph (`og:title`, `og:image`, `og:video`) and Twitter Card metadata.

#### [MODIFY] [app/profile/[username]/page.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/app/profile/[username]/page.tsx)
- Export [generateMetadata](file:///C:/GOLive/app/profile/%5Busername%5D/page.tsx#17-64) function.
- Fetch profile data and populate OG tags with the creator's avatar and bio.

### Performance (Lazy Loading)
#### [MODIFY] [components/VideoCard.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/components/VideoCard.tsx)
- Implement a custom `useIntersectionObserver` hook (or use `react-intersection-observer` if installed, otherwise vanilla `IntersectionObserver`).
- Only load the `img src` for the thumbnail when the card is within 100px of the viewport.
- Maintain a beautiful skeleton state while the thumbnail is out of view or loading.

### UX Optimization (Background Uploads)

Currently, users must wait on the `/upload` page while their video processes. We will implement "fire and forget" uploads.

#### [NEW] `components/UploadProvider.tsx`
- A React Context that wraps the application.
- Houses the multi-part R2 upload logic and `/api/process` call previously found in [upload/page.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/app/upload/page.tsx).
- Maps internal upload progress to a globally visible Toast locked to the bottom margin of the viewport.

#### [MODIFY] [app/layout.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/app/layout.tsx)
- Wrap children with `<UploadProvider>`.

#### [MODIFY] [app/upload/page.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/app/upload/page.tsx)
- Strip the inline upload logic.
- Consume `startUpload` from `UploadProvider`.
- Upon form submission, instantly redirect the user to `/studio/dashboard` while the UploadProvider handles the rest in the background.

## Verification Plan
### Automated Tests
- Inspect the `<head>` tag of a rendered Watch page to verify `og:image` and `twitter:card` tags are present and populated with the correct video data.
- Use Chrome DevTools Network tab (with disabled cache) to verify that thumbnails below the fold are NOT downloaded until scrolled into view.

### Manual Verification
- **Uploads**: Initiate a video upload, immediately navigate to the `Trending` page, and verify that the global upload toast accurately tracks the upload and processing phases without halting.
